⁵ Velle et censere] Velle proprie populus dicebatur, censere senatus· Sed inum etiam, etsi raro, de senatu dicitur.—-M.

XXII. ¹ BIaturantes veniunt] See Perizon. ad Sanct. 3, 10, note 1, giving examples of an active participle joined to a substantive verb, and Sanct. himself.—C.

² Run or clemens] Clemens dicitur rumor, quando rem non exagss gerat, aut infra atrocitatem res est—M.

³ Accepta oratione] Orator anciently signified an ambassador or messenger, and hence oratione was used to denote the message or oom- mission. The supine, oratum, signified to execute the embassy, or de- liver the message, i. e. to beg aid or peace. Cap. 24, Ad vos oratum mitto. See cap. 108, note L—M.
